## рҹ“Ұ Phase 1: Core Engine Foundation

### 1.1 Project Setup
- Vite + TypeScript project
- Three.js setup (WebGLRenderer, PerspectiveCamera, Scene)
- Game loop with fixed physics timestep (50ms / 20 TPS)
- Input manager (keyboard + mouse)

### 1.2 Block System
- `BlockRegistry` вҖ” all block types with properties
- Block types:

| Block | ID | Hardness | Tool | Drop |
|-------|-----|----------|------|------|
| Air | 0 | вҖ” | вҖ” | вҖ” |
| Grass | 1 | 0.6 | Shovel | Dirt |
| Dirt | 2 | 0.5 | Shovel | Dirt |
| Stone | 3 | 1.5 | Pickaxe | Cobblestone |
| Cobblestone | 4 | 2.0 | Pickaxe | Cobblestone |
| Oak Log | 5 | 2.0 | Axe | Oak Log |
| Oak Leaves | 6 | 0.2 | Shears | вҖ” |
| Oak Planks | 7 | 2.0 | Axe | Oak Planks |
| Bedrock | 8 | вҲһ | вҖ” | вҖ” |
| Sand | 9 | 0.5 | Shovel | Sand |
| Gravel | 10 | 0.6 | Shovel | Gravel |
| Coal Ore | 11 | 3.0 | Pickaxe | Coal |
| Iron Ore | 12 | 3.0 | Pickaxe | Iron Ore |
| Gold Ore | 13 | 3.0 | Pickaxe | Gold Ore |
| Diamond Ore | 14 | 3.0 | Pickaxe | Diamond Ore |
| Water | 15 | вҖ” | вҖ” | вҖ” |
| Glass | 16 | 0.3 | вҖ” | вҖ” |
| Crafting Table | 17 | 2.5 | Axe | Crafting Table |
| Furnace | 18 | 3.5 | Pickaxe | Furnace |
| Chest | 19 | 2.5 | Axe | Chest |

### 1.3 Chunk System
- Chunk size: **16 Г— 256 Г— 16** blocks
- Flat 1D array storage: `blocks[x + z*16 + y*16*16]`
- Chunk coordinates: world position Г· 16
- Render distance: 8 chunks (configurable)

### 1.4 Greedy Meshing
- Only generate faces between solid and non-solid blocks
- Merge adjacent same-type faces into larger quads (greedy mesh)
- Per-chunk `BufferGeometry` with:
  - Position attribute
  - Normal attribute
  - UV attribute (texture atlas coordinates)
  - AO (ambient occlusion) from neighboring blocks

### 1.5 Texture Atlas
- 16Г—16 pixel block textures
- Single atlas texture (256Г—256 or 512Г—512)
- UV mapping per block face (top, bottom, sides can differ)

### 1.6 Player Controller
- **PointerLock API** for mouse capture
- First-person camera
- WASD movement (walk, sprint with Shift)
- Space = Jump, gravity = 32 blocks/sВІ
- AABB collision detection against blocks
- Walking speed: 4.317 blocks/s, Sprint: 5.612 blocks/s

---

## рҹ“Ұ Phase 2: Block Interaction

### 2.1 Raycasting
- Cast ray from camera center
- Max reach: 5 blocks
- Highlight targeted block face
- Show wireframe outline on target block

### 2.2 Block Breaking
- Left click = start mining
- Mining progress bar overlay
- **Break time** = `blockHardness Г— toolMultiplier`
- Tool multipliers:

| Tool Tier | Multiplier |
|-----------|------------|
| Hand | Г—1.0 |
| Wood | Г—2.0 |
| Stone | Г—4.0 |
| Iron | Г—6.0 |
| Diamond | Г—8.0 |

- Breaking animation: 10 stages (crack overlay texture)
- Block particles on break (3D particles flying out)
- Drop item entity on break

### 2.3 Block Placing
- Right click = place block from hotbar
- Place against the face being looked at
- Cannot place inside player hitbox
- Deduct 1 from hotbar stack

### 2.4 Item Entities
- Dropped items float and rotate in world
- Picked up when player walks near (1.5 block radius)
- Auto-stack into inventory
- Despawn after 5 minutes

---

## рҹ“Ұ Phase 3: World Generation

### 3.1 Terrain Height
```
height(x, z) = baseHeight 
  + noise2D(x/100, z/100) * 30     // Mountains
  + noise2D(x/50, z/50) * 15       // Hills  
  + noise2D(x/25, z/25) * 5        // Details
```
- Base height: 64
- Min: ~40, Max: ~120, Sea level: 62

### 3.2 Block Layers
```
y == height        вҶ’ Grass (or Sand if near water)
height-4 < y < height вҶ’ Dirt
y < height-4       вҶ’ Stone
y == 0              вҶ’ Bedrock
y < 5               вҶ’ Bedrock (random)
```

### 3.3 Cave Generation
- 3D Simplex noise with threshold:
  ```
  cave(x, y, z) = noise3D(x/30, y/30, z/30)
  if cave > 0.6 вҶ’ carve out (set to Air)
  ```
- Don't carve surface blocks (y > height - 3)
- Lava at y < 10 (stretch goal)

### 3.4 Ore Generation
| Ore | Min Y | Max Y | Vein Size | Frequency |
|-----|-------|-------|-----------|-----------|
| Coal | 0 | 128 | 8-12 | Common |
| Iron | 0 | 64 | 4-8 | Moderate |
| Gold | 0 | 32 | 4-6 | Rare |
| Diamond | 0 | 16 | 2-4 | Very Rare |

- Ores only replace Stone blocks
- Vein algorithm: random walk from seed point

### 3.5 Tree Generation
- Oak trees on grass blocks
- Probability: ~1 per 50 surface blocks
- Structure:
  - Trunk: 4-6 blocks tall (Oak Log)
  - Crown: 5Г—5Г—3 leaf dome on top
  - No trees too close together (min 3 blocks apart)

### 3.6 Water
- Water fills all blocks below sea level (y=62) that are Air
- Water is translucent (alpha blending)
- Simple side faces with slightly darker shade
- Swimming mechanics: slower movement, floating

### 3.7 Clouds
- 2D layer at y=128
- Semi-transparent white blocks
- Slowly drifting (animated UV offset)
- Generated from 2D noise

